.TH "CIRCLECI-MIGRATE" "1" "Jun 2026" "circleci-migrate" "CircleCI Org Migration CLI"

.SH NAME
circleci-migrate - Migrate data between CircleCI organisations.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcircleci-migrate [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
circleci-migrate helps you move data — contexts, project settings,
environment variables, and more — from one CircleCI organisation to another.

.PP
Typical workflow:
.IP "  1." 5
Export the source organisation to a local manifest file:
   circleci-migrate export --source-token $SRC_TOKEN --org gh/myorg
.IP "  2." 5
(Optional) Review or edit the manifest.
.IP "  3." 5
Sync the manifest into the destination organisation (the destination org is
 inferred from the manifest; no --org flag is needed):
   circleci-migrate sync  --dest-token $DST_TOKEN --manifest manifest.json --apply

.PP
Or run both steps in one shot:
       circleci-migrate migrate --source-token $SRC_TOKEN --dest-token $DST_TOKEN \\
         --source-org gh/myorg --dest-org gh/neworg

.PP
Use "circleci-migrate [command] --help" for more information about a command.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug logging

.PP
\fB--dest-token\fP=""
	API token for the destination org (env: CIRCLECI_DEST_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for circleci-migrate

.PP
\fB--host\fP="https://circleci.com"
	CircleCI host URL (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_HOST, CIRCLECI_HOST, or CIRCLE_URL)

.PP
\fB--source-token\fP=""
	API token for the source org (env: CIRCLECI_SOURCE_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	Personal API token — fallback for both orgs (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_TOKEN or CIRCLE_TOKEN)


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcircleci-migrate-export(1)\fP, \fBcircleci-migrate-migrate(1)\fP, \fBcircleci-migrate-orb(1)\fP, \fBcircleci-migrate-secrets(1)\fP, \fBcircleci-migrate-sync(1)\fP, \fBcircleci-migrate-version(1)\fP
